.\" Man page for _pritnf
.TH _PRINTF 3 "March 2026" "man_3_printf"
.SH NAME
_printf \- custom printf function

.SH REQUIREMENTS TO USE
#include "main.h"

int _printf(const char *format, ...);

Also, if you must view this man page, i like to use ' groff -man -Tascii man_3_printf | less '

.SH DESCRIPTION
This functions acts as a simplified printf standard function.

It writes out a standard output by using write.

The format string can handle text and these conversion specifiers:

.TP
%c
Characters

.TP
%s
Strings

.TP
%d and %i
Integers

.TP
%%
Prints a percentage sign

If extra arguments are given such as _printf("hello %s\n", "world", 1, 2, 3, 4) they are ignored

If a percentage sign is at the end of 'format' it is ignored

.SH RETURN VALUE
If the return goes through, _printf returns the number of characters printed (excluding the null byte)

.SH EXAMPLES
_printf("hello %s\n", "world", 1, 2, 3, 4);
.br
Output: hello world

_printf("Jay Z's problems: %i\n", 99);
.br
Output: Jay Z's problems: 99

_printf("%");
.br
There is no output here

.SH LIMITATIONS
If a converter that isnt used in the project is given, eg %x, it will simply print %x as the code isnt set up to handle these specifiers.
.br
Other more complex flags are ignored. 
